"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1934924-Olympics-2024-Daniel-Wiffen-hospital\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Irish swimmer Daniel Wiffen has been rushed to hospital after being forced to miss theParis 2024 Olympicsclosing ceremony due to illness.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2, \"end\": 7, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9925884240091278, \"rank\": 0.005032226432643745, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wiffen secured two medals in Paris, including gold for his nation in the 800m freestyleat La Defense Arena, making history as the first Irish man to win an Olympic gold medal in the swimming pool.\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 337, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 170, \"end\": 175, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999996479346, \"rank\": 3.5207273058145136e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 231, \"end\": 241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_D\\u00e9fense\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"La Defense\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_D\\u00e9fense\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_D\\u00e9fense\"}, {\"begin\": 277, \"end\": 282, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9925884240091278, \"rank\": 0.005032226432643745, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympian was nominated to carry his nation's flag in the ceremony at the Stade de France, only to withdraw hours before the event began on Sunday after becoming \\\"very unwell\\\".\", \"from\": 339, \"to\": 518, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 343, \"end\": 351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999969611508, \"rank\": 3.038769848575488e-09, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wiffen also won a bronze medal for Ireland competing in the 1,500m freestyle, before taking part in the challenging 10km swim through the River Seine.\", \"from\": 520, \"to\": 670, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 555, \"end\": 562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9959680230847905, \"rank\": 0.004030150635872421, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 658, \"end\": 669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Serious concerns had been raised throughout the 16-day Olympic competition about the state of the dirty water in the Seine, with daily measures carried out by Olympic officials to check for possible contaminates such as the bacteria E.coli.\", \"from\": 672, \"to\": 912, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 789, \"end\": 794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999710278193, \"rank\": 2.0214640891992603e-08, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 23-year-old, who was born in Leeds, posted a message on social media thanking fans for their messages after missing the closing ceremony.\", \"from\": 914, \"to\": 1055, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 947, \"end\": 952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leeds\", \"score\": 0.8711787676574221, \"rank\": 0.14658779325994667, \"text\": \"Leeds\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leeds\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leeds\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Thanks everyone who reached out, I am incredibly disappointed to miss out on the opportunity to be flag bearer last night,\\\" Wiffen wrote on X, formerly Twitter.\", \"from\": 1059, \"to\": 1220, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Yesterday I rushed to hospital as I was very unwell with a bug that I am being treated for, and am feeling better now.\", \"from\": 1222, \"to\": 1341, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I hope everyone enjoys the evening and I hope to be well enough to seeing everyone when we get home.\\\"\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1443, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is not yet clear what caused Wiffen to contract the bug, although he is not the first athlete to have swam in the polluted Seine River and later suffer from illness.\", \"from\": 1445, \"to\": 1613, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thanks everyone who reached out, I am incredibly disappointed to miss out on the opportunity to be flag bearer last night.Yesterday I rushed to hospital as I was very unwell with a bug that I am being treated for, and am feeling better now.\", \"from\": 1615, \"to\": 1855, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I hope everyone enjoys the evening\\u2026  Three German swimmers were struck down after competing in open water races during the Olympics, although it has not been confirmed that the swim was directly responsible for their sickness.\", \"from\": 1856, \"to\": 2082, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1899, \"end\": 1905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 0.6683023598710427, \"rank\": 0.4929427382063572, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We use your sign-up to provide content in ways you have consented to and to improve our understanding of you.\", \"from\": 2084, \"to\": 2193, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This may include adverts from us and 3rd parties based on our understanding.\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2270, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can unsubscribe at any time.\", \"from\": 2271, \"to\": 2303, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy Policy  With Wiffen absent from the ceremony as fans gathered for the final event of the Olympics, Fintan McCarthy - who won gold in the rowing event - stepped in alongside bronze medallist Mona McSharry for Ireland at the closing ceremony.\", \"from\": 2304, \"to\": 2560, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2510, \"end\": 2523, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_McSharry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mona McSharry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_McSharry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_McSharry\"}, {\"begin\": 2528, \"end\": 2535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9959680230847905, \"rank\": 0.004030150635872421, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McSharry and Wiffen became their nation's second and third Olympic swimming medallists after Wiffen as Ireland secured seven podium finishes in Paris - their highest total to date.\", \"from\": 2562, \"to\": 2742, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2665, \"end\": 2672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9959680230847905, \"rank\": 0.004030150635872421, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q